<headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued August 07 at 2:37PM EDT until August 08 at 2:00AM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 AM EDT
TUESDAY...
* WHAT...High wave action, strong currents, and dangerous
swimming conditions expected. Piers may be heavily swamped by
waves.
* WHERE...Mason, Oceana, Muskegon, Ottawa, Allegan and Van Buren
counties.
* WHEN...Through late tonight.
* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Waves will build quickly mid-late this
afternoon, especially south of Muskegon. The north side of piers
and structures will be the most hazardous. Holland State Park
and North Beach in South Haven will be the most impacted.</description>
<instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions
and do not venture out on piers. Please check with your local
authorities on potential beach closures.</instruction>
